data.description: The "hash" parameter describes the expected short URL (may be omitted for random generation) : http://opn.to/a/{hash}. The "data.url" parameter describes the destination URL.

data.name: Live URL update

data.name: QR Code creation
data.description: The "label" parameter describes the name of the QR Code, as displayed in the Unitag Dashboard. The "live" parameter is the ID of a previously created Live URL. The "settings" parameter describes the QR Code design (documentation: https://github.com/unitag/QRCODES-API/blob/master/documentation.md#setting-object).

data.name: QR Code update
data.description: The "label" parameter describes the new name of the QR Code, as displayed in the Unitag Dashboard. The "settings" parameter describes the new QR Code design (documentation: https://github.com/unitag/QRCODES-API/blob/master/documentation.md#setting-object).

data.name: hash
data.description: Hash for which the availability is to be tested
This endpoint allows to check the availability of a given hash. This hash can then be used to create a Live URL of the following form: http://opn.to/a/{hash}.

response.name: Hash availability check
response.description: If the hash is available, the result is an empty 200 response.
